participating-org.narrative: Hivos is an NGO based in the Netherlands and guided by humanist values. It wants to contribute to a free, fair and sustainable world where citizens, women and men, have equal access to resources, opportunities and markets and can participate actively and equally in decision-making processes that shape their lives, their society and their future. Hivos' basic commitment is to poor and marginalised people -and their organisations- in countries in South and Eastern Europe. A sustainable improvement in their situation is the ultimate benchmark for the work and efforts of Hivos. The empowerment of women in order to achieve gender equality is a primary directive in Hivos' policy. Hivos aim is a world in which people are equal and in which no limits are set on people's opportunities for development. To that end Hivos offers financial support to civil society organisations and initiatives that share Hivos' goals. In addition to funding, Hivos networks, lobbies and shares knowledge in the international arena, as well as in the Netherlands. Hivos relates to a diversity of actors in civil society, and seeks its alliances in different domains (economy, culture, human rights, gender equality and environment) and in different hemispheres. In the Netherlands, in Europe and worldwide it joins forces with like-minded organisations that share the same goals.
